.nh
.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "May 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-migrate-v4 - Migrate agent profiles and config to v4.0 format


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira migrate v4 [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Migrate agent profiles to the v4.0 format by assigning tier fields.

.PP
Agent profiles without a tier field are automatically assigned a tier based
on their existing capabilities:
.IP \(bu 2
Profiles with CanRunCommands=true  → admin tier
.IP \(bu 2
Profiles with CanWrite=true        → standard tier
.IP \(bu 2
All other profiles                 → safe tier

.PP
The original config is backed up as config.yaml.v3-backup-
before any changes are written.

.PP
This migration is idempotent — running it multiple times is safe for
profiles that already have a tier field.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--dry-run\fP[=false]
	Preview changes without writing

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for v4

.PP
\fB-y\fP, \fB--yes\fP[=false]
	Skip confirmation prompt


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--color\fP="auto"
	When to emit ANSI color: auto, always, never

.PP
\fB--no-pipe-warning\fP[=false]
	suppress 'reading from non-TTY' warning when piping secrets

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	Output format (text, json, yaml)

.PP
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--theme\fP=""
	Color preset: default, highcontrast, colorblind (or OPENPASS_THEME)

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH EXAMPLE
.EX
  openpass migrate v4
  openpass migrate v4 --dry-run
  openpass migrate v4 --yes
.EE


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBsymaira-migrate(1)\fP
